        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 7:05PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 705 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northeast of Wellington, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wellington and Dodson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
